	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok..  I have seen a lot of incorrect information on the board here so here is the whole thing, everything about Mr. Hermit, and it's all right!<BR>
<BR>
He is level 20, always.  He is a ranger (Not a druid!).  Soon as he spawns, he casts thistlecoat on himself.  This is a self-only buff, damage shield and AC buff (1 point damage shield).  He also casts a fire based spell during fighting, I believe burst of flame.  There are no faction hits for killing him.  His max hit seems to be 42, whether he's holding FS or not.<BR>
<BR>
He is in a little house in South Karana, location is: neg5500, neg 2600 rounded off<BR>
<BR>
His 'house' is a round stone wall with a door, with a house inside that.  There are multiple ways to fight him:<BR>
1) Target through the door and cast any spell.  Easiest way.<BR>
2) Walk near the house (by the chimney or right at the door seems to work best) and say anything with the words 'kill you'.  This will aggro him.<BR>
*NOTE*   All NPCs have the 'warp' ability now in that if they run for a set time and don't move towards you, they will instantly warp to your exact location.  This will happen always unless he just happens to make it through the little crack in the door.<BR>
3) Walk up to the wall of the (inside) house, and cast treeform.  Press walk forward, and then cancel treeform, you'll fall through the wall inside the house.  From there targeting and attacking is easy.    CAREFUL You will have to gate out , can't get out of the house the same way.  An enchanter form may also be able to accomplish this.<BR>
<BR>
My favorite way to kill him (currently lvl22 druid):<BR>
Use the treeform trick to get inside.  That's just fun :).  Once inside, go right in front of him and put up treeform.  Five hitpoints per tick regen that only costs 30 mana and lasts forever is great!   Wait for him to spawn if not up, medding.  Starting full health and mana when he spawns, put Shield of Barbs along with Barbcoat on (I keep myself fully buffed with Skin like Rock/Thistlecoat/Firefist/Strength of Earth/Barbcoat).  Cast stinging swarm on him, and start swinging your weapon of choice.  While he's hitting on you and taking 10 damage for each hit, work in a few careless lightnings and a snare.  Melee the last 20% after he's running, and you're left around three bubbles of mana and health still remainging.  Med (still in treeform the whole time) and you're fh/fm by the time he's spawned!  Great experience.<BR>
<BR>
I've noted though that he drops far less FS weapons than he once used to.  He also drops 'Winds of Karana Sheet 1' and 'A Cracked Flute' (that weighs 10 stone, damn heavy flute).  Take the flute to Cordelia Minister who is a bard npc in NK that usually hangs out at the wizzie spires.  She'll give you wind of karana sheet two.  Take both of these sheets to Vhalen Nostrolo back in South Karana and he rewards you with a random bard song.  I've gotten the level 1 to level 5 songs so far, but have only done this about 4 times.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
